				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Lv 60 Bards...<a name="1496"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 13 02 6:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Winning BotB means very little about bard skill. It does mean that your friend is uberly equipped though.
<br />

<br />
I mentioned it in s thread on the main site but 2 common twists I use are:-
<br />
(AA)+VCoC+BoH+cantata+warsong (no haste); and
<br />
(AA)+warsong+BoH+cantata+fufil+flame/frost
<br />

<br />
One thing to bear in mind here is  that I do not have an epic to rely on for haste. If I did I might be inclined to play with katta or CoB until it procs, and to switch between 2 different twists depending on whether the epic haste is on or off.
<br />

<br />
Another thing to bear in mind is the types of encounters you and your friend are engaged in. As I said above it seems clear to me that your frienc is uberly equipped. As such he is probably raiding alot, especially on mobs that are either unslowable, or that hit quickly even when slowed.
<br />

<br />
In this case a DS twist of the type he suggests is usually the best option when you are in the MT grp. In fact parses of Vindi-like mobs has shown bards consistently outdamaging rogues by using DS tactics. This strategy is much less effective in normal xp situations, and even on lower-end raid encounters.
<br />

<br />
It sounds to me that what you are doing is correct for the stage of the game that you are in. It is well to understand how things change when you move up to the next stage of encounters, but that shouldn't stop you from playing what is working for you right now.
<br />

<br />
(-:   Zel  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />
</span></td>
